cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.SY

The paper discusses Artificial Immune Systems (AIS) and their application to combinatorial optimization problems. This falls under the category of computational intelligence and optimization, which is covered by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of hypermutations and their potential, which is related to optimization algorithms and their performance, covered by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the use of ageing in the AIS, which is related to control and systems engineering, covered by cs.SY (Systems and Control).
